From 8c1f503841f9655feb00b54515e5774e8b19abab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 1 Dec 2025 06:54:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 18/73] drm/panthor: Add Sky1 platform-specific initialization

Add CIX Sky1 (Mali-G720) specific initialization code ported from
vendor kernel 6.6:

- Add cix,sky1-mali to device table
- Add reset control and RCSU region mapping
- Add PHBA configuration (GPU_SYSC_ALLOC registers)
- Add LS_MEM counter workaround for performance counters
- Add PWR_OVERRIDE1 power transition latency settings
- Add PM domain performance state forcing
- Disable Q-channel clock gating (vendor doesn't use RCSU 0x218)

The GPU initializes successfully but jobs timeout on first submission.
The CSG update times out suggesting firmware communication issues.
Further investigation needed for the cache flush mechanism difference
between mainline (GPU_CONTROL.FLUSH_CACHES) and vendor (AS_COMMAND).
